Package: fll-installer
Architecture: all
Pre-Depends: dpkg (>= 1.14.6)
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 adduser,
 initramfs-tools,
 grub-pc (>= 1.96+20080601-1),
 procps,
 udev-config-aptosid,
 whois,
 os-prober,
 rsync,
 fll-live-initscripts (>= 2.0.72)
Recommends: install-gui
Suggests: gparted,
 distro-defaults
Description: backend scripts to install aptosid to hdd
 fll-installer provides a framework for installing FULLSTORY Live Linux
 to hard disk drives.
 .
 This is a FULLSTORY live-only package and should not be installed to an
 ordinary system.

Package: fll-iso2usb
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 grub-pc (>= 1.96+20080601-1) | grub-legacy | grub-gfxboot,
 distro-defaults,
 parted
Recommends: install-usb-gui
Suggests: fuseiso
Enhances: qt-fll-iso2usb-gui,
 install-usb-gui
Description: backend scripts to install aptosid to an usb hdd
 fll-iso2usb provides the backend for installing FULLSTORY Live Linux aptosid to
 removable storage, usb disk drives.
 .
 This preserves a hardware agnostic live system on removable storage.
